and general method for exploration in such problems. GLIB samples goals that
are conjunctions of literals, which can be understood as specific, targeted
effects that the agent would like to achieve in the world, and plans to achieve
these goals using the operators being learned. We conduct a case study to
elucidate two key benefits of GLIB: robustness to overly general preconditions
