advection-diffusion-reaction equation, a finite medium comprising an arbitrary
number of layers, continuity of concentration and diffusive flux at the
interfaces between adjacent layers and transient boundary conditions of
arbitrary type at the two boundaries. Our derived semi-analytical solution
extends and addresses deficiencies of existing Laplace-transform based
solutions in a layered medium, which consider diffusion or reaction-diffusion
